<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 1:58PM MDT until June 28 at 2:30PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Great Falls has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Madison County in southwestern Montana...
North central Beaverhead County in southwestern Montana...
* Until 230 PM MDT.
* At 158 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles south of
Twin Bridges, or 13 miles southwest of Sheridan, moving northeast
at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Sheridan, Twin Bridges, Silver Star and Laurin.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
